com.acmerobotics.roadrunner.kinematics

Class MecanumKinematics

  • com.acmerobotics.roadrunner.kinematics.MecanumKinematics

  • public class MecanumKinematics

    Mecanum drive kinematic equations. All wheel positions and velocities are given starting with front left and proceeding counter-clockwise (i.e., front left, rear left, rear right, front right). Robot poses are specified in a coordinate system with positive x pointing forward, positive y pointing left, and positive heading measured counter-clockwise from the x-axis.

    This paper provides a motivated derivation.

    See Also:
    This paper

      • robotToWheelVelocities

        @JvmStatic
 @JvmOverloads
 @NotNull
public static java.util.List<java.lang.Double> robotToWheelVelocities(@NotNull
                                                                                                          Pose2d robotVel,
                                                                                                          double trackWidth,
                                                                                                          double wheelBase,
                                                                                                          double lateralMultiplier)

        Computes the wheel velocities corresponding to robotVel given the provided trackWidth and wheelBase.

        Parameters:
        robotVel - velocity of the robot in its reference frame
        trackWidth - lateral distance between pairs of wheels on different sides of the robot
        wheelBase - distance between pairs of wheels on the same side of the robot
        lateralMultiplier - multiplicative gain to adjust for systematic, proportional lateral error (gain greaterthan 1.0 corresponds to overcompensation).
        See Also:
        robotVel, trackWidth, wheelBase
